Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{80%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @British pork loin steaks{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once hot, add the pork steaks. Fry until browned, ~{2-3%mins} on each side.

Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{4-6%mins}, turning every couple of mins.

Once cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with another plate or #foil{} to rest.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the pork rests, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

As it boils, return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of oil (no need to clean).

Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @fresh pesto{32%g} and @water{} for the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until thickened slightly, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%mins}.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Bring back to the boil, then add the beans and cook until just tender, ~{4-6%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, then return to the saucepan. Season with salt and pepper. Toss in @olive oil{drizzle}.

When ready, transfer your pork steaks to your plates.

Serve with your roasted potatoes and green beans alongside.

Finish by spooning the pesto sauce over the pork (reheat first if needed).

Enjoy!